 Port Elizabeth - Some good rains were recorded in the catchment areas of the Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality according to data released by the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service on Tuesday. "Although only between 3 and 10 mm fell in Port Elizabeth, the Langkloof catchment area had between 10 mm at Joubertina and 15 mm at Kareedouw," described Garth Sampson, the SA Weather Service's Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape. "Conditions are expected to clear from later this morning." 2019/10/01 Station Names 22 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 3.0 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 4.6 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 5.8 ARS Chatty 5.0 AWS Coega 1.8 AWSH Fettes Road 4.8 ARS Flower Reserve 9.8 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 4.8 ARS St Albans 7.2 AWS Uitenhage 5.4 Man Woodridge 6.8 Catchment  AWS Joubertina 10.2 ARS Kareedouw 14.8 Man Kareedouw 15.0 Man Kouga Dam 5.6 AWS Patensie 2.6    Other Towns  AWS Addo 1.0 AWS Bisho/KWT 0.0 AWS Cape St Francis 2.0 AWS Cradock NIL AWS East London NIL AWS Fort Beaufort 0.6 AWS George 7.5 AWS Graaff Reinet NIL AWS Grahamstown 1.6 AWS Henry`s Flats 0.8 AWS Joubertina 10.2 AWS Mossel Bay 0.8 AWS Mthatha NIL AWS Plettenberg bay 2.6 AWS Port Alfred 1.2 AWS Queenstown NIL * no contact 0.0 = Drops  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 